<TITLE> Khaleda heads for Rajshahi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia left Dhaka for Rajshahi on Wednesday morning to attend a divisional meeting. The opposition leader will address the meeting at around 3pm at Alia Madrasa ground of the district city, which will be her first speech in the city since Dec 29, 2008 national elections. The BNP chief's convoy, which includes party vice president Selima Rahman, left her cantonment residence at around 9am, her press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan told bdnews24.om. This is the third of six grand rallies across the country. The first rally was held in Chittagong on Mar 29 and the second one in Khulna on Apr 18. BNP standing committee member Goyeshwar Chandra Roy speaking from Rajshahi, told bdnews24.com all preparations were complete. In her speech, Khaleda is expected to raise issues about the criminal activities of the ruling party, tender manipulation, harassment of women, spiralling rate of essentials, crises of water, gas and power and vote rigging in the recent Bhola-3 by polls, Roy said. BNP will hold the next meetings in Barisal and Dhaka on May 12 and 19. The last meeting will be held in Sylhet. 
